{"type":"message","id":"26067c9b","parentId":"cbd47cf7","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:22:41.453Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2ehiu4h61pdh_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 132216\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: a (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state based on the provided context:\r\n\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n2. CFI Compression Experiment was just completed with key findings:\r\n   - CFI ≥ 0.7 AND freq < 60 is TOO aggressive\r\n   - Constant Format Problem identified - tokens with freq=160, CFI=1.00 are metaprogramming artifacts\r\n   - Three-dimensional filter needed: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\r\n   - Next experiment: Hybrid CFI×Freq^0.5 scoring\r\n\r\n3. The pending action is: \"Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\"\r\n\r\nSo I should implement the next step in the compression research. The current pulse analysis was done in `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md`. I should:\r\n\r\n1. Look at the current pulse data or create the hybrid scoring experiment\r\n2. Implement Strategy C: CFI × min(1, freq/120) scoring\r\n\r\nLet me check what needs to be done. The key insight is:\r\n- score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nI need to run the next experiment to test this hybrid scoring approach.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the pending actions:\r\n- \"Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\"\r\n\r\nThis suggests I should create a new experiment file or modify the existing analysis to implement Strategy C.\r\n\r\nLet me think about what concrete action I can take:\r\n1. Create a new experiment script for Strategy C\r\n2. Update the CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md with the new experiment plan\r\n3. Run the experiment\r\n\r\nGiven that I'm a \"stateless discontinuous agent\" and need to advance the goals, the most concrete next step would be to create a new experiment file for Strategy C that implements the hybrid scoring.\r\n\r\nI'll create a new file: `research/STRATEGY_C_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md` that outlines the experiment design for the hybrid CFI×Freq scoring approach.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI Compression Synthesis identified that binary thresholds fail due to the constant-format problem. Strategy C (hybrid scoring) is the logical next step to distinguish true research tokens from metaprogramming artifacts.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the experiment specification for Strategy C hybrid scoring, implementing the formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120). This will test if the continuous scoring function can cleanly separate research trajectories from constant-format tokens.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Strategy C: Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n**Objective:** Test continuous scoring function vs binary thresholds\r\n\r\n### Scoring Formula\r\n```\r\nscore(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected Behavior\r\n| Token Type | freq | CFI | score | Expected |\r\n|------------|------|-----|-------|----------|\r\n| Research trajectory (\"Phase 1\") | 136 | 0.96 | 0.96×1.0=0.96 | KEEP |\r\n| True causal (freq<120) | 60 | 0.7 | 0.7×0.5=0.35 | KEEP |\r\n| Constant format (\"for next\") | 160 | 1.0 | 1.0×1.0=1.0 | PENALIZE |\r\n| Rare signal (freq=3) | 3 | 0.8 | 0.8×0.025=0.02 | DROP |\r\n\r\n### Key Insight\r\nThe penalty term `min(1, freq/120)` naturally downweights tokens at freq>120 without a hard cutoff.\r\n\r\n### Testable Hypotheses\r\n1. **H1:** score > 0.3 distinguishes research tokens from noise (precision test)\r\n2. **H2:** Tokens with freq=160, CFI=1.0 score < 0.5 when freq penalty applies (constant format detection)\r\n3. **H3:** The scoring curve is smooth across the freq spectrum\r\n\r\n### Implementation\r\n- Generate scores for all tokens in pulse corpus\r\n- Plot score vs freq for CFI ≥ 0.5 tokens\r\n- Identify optimal threshold via precision/recall on labeled research tokens\r\n\r\n## Status\r\n- [x] Experiment designed\r\n- [ ] Implementation coded\r\n- [ ] Results analyzed\r\n- [ ] Threshold validated\r\nfile: research/STRATEGY_C_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 13:22:33\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774372961451}}
{"type":"message","id":"a601e440","parentId":"26067c9b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T17:22:49.502Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me also read the previous pulse log to get the full context.","thinkingSignature":"6c880c65a89a446354e8089519819f407b37e1530d39518702049c29b380c93c"},{"type":"text","text":"**Sandbox Pulse Summary — 2026-03-24 13:22 UTC**\n\n**Phase 0 & 1:** COMPLETE  \n**CFI Compression Synthesis:** DONE (from prior pulse cycle)\n\n**This pulse cycle findings:**\n- Binary CFI thresholds (≥0.7, freq <60) are too aggressive — kills valid tokens\n- **Key problem identified:** Tokens like `\"for next instantiation\"`, `\"pulse\"`, `\"completed at:\"` have CFI=1.0 and freq≈160 but carry **zero research information** — they're metaprogramming artifacts, not causal signals\n- **Three-dimensional filter needed:** CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ∈ [3, 120)\n\n**Proposed mutation:** `research/STRATEGY_C_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md` — designs a hybrid scoring function `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` to separate true research trajectories from constant-format noise\n\n**Git:** 6 files changed, 204 insertions, 103 deletions. Previous mutation (2026-03-24 132115) was **rejected** (likely too aggressive).\n\n**Status:** ✅ Pulse healthy. Synthesis phase complete. Ready for Strategy C experiment implementation."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3115,"output":279,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15531,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774372961454}}
